{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":39,"text":"Over the last two decades, India has become"},{"time":3013,"text":"a global hub for software development"},{"time":6052,"text":"and offshoring of back office services, as we call it,"},{"time":10079,"text":"and what we were interested in finding out was that"},{"time":15099,"text":"because of this huge industry that has started"},{"time":19039,"text":"over the last two decades in India,"},{"time":21050,"text":"offshoring software development and back office services,"},{"time":24041,"text":"there's been a flight of white collar jobs"},{"time":26064,"text":"from the developed world to India."},{"time":30015,"text":"When this is combined with the loss of manufacturing jobs"},{"time":33071,"text":"to China, it has, you know, led to considerable angst"},{"time":37001,"text":"amongst the Western populations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40089,"text":"In fact, if you look at polls, they show a declining"},{"time":43051,"text":"trend for support for free trade in the West."},{"time":48087,"text":"Now, the Western elites, however, have said"},{"time":51086,"text":"this fear is misplaced."},{"time":53086,"text":"For example, if you have read — I suspect many of you"},{"time":56008,"text":"have done so — read the book by Thomas Friedman"},{"time":59040,"text":"called \"The World Is Flat,\" he said, basically, in his book"},{"time":62074,"text":"that, you know, this fear for free trade is wrong"},{"time":66093,"text":"because it assumes, it's based on a mistaken assumption"},{"time":69067,"text":"that everything that can be invented has been invented."},{"time":73051,"text":"In fact, he says, it's innovation that will keep the West"},{"time":76037,"text":"ahead of the developing world,"},{"time":78010,"text":"with the more sophisticated, innovative tasks being done"},{"time":81052,"text":"in the developed world, and the less sophisticated,"},{"time":84025,"text":"shall we say, drudge work being done"},{"time":85083,"text":"in the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88099,"text":"Now, what we were trying to understand was,"},{"time":92031,"text":"is this true?"},{"time":95007,"text":"Could India become a source, or a global hub,"},{"time":98086,"text":"of innovation, just like it's become a global hub"},{"time":102003,"text":"for back office services and software development?"},{"time":105090,"text":"And for the last four years, my coauthor Phanish Puranam"},{"time":109072,"text":"and I spent investigating this topic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113002,"text":"Initially, or, you know, as people would say, you know,"},{"time":117002,"text":"in fact the more aggressive people who are supporting"},{"time":119043,"text":"the Western innovative model, say,"},{"time":121069,"text":"\"Where are the Indian Googles, iPods and Viagras,"},{"time":124027,"text":"if the Indians are so bloody smart?\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":128053,"text":"So initially, when we started our research, we went"},{"time":130088,"text":"and met several executives, and we asked them,"},{"time":132098,"text":"\"What do you think? Will India go from being a favored"},{"time":135027,"text":"destination for software services and back office services"},{"time":138027,"text":"to a destination for innovation?\""},{"time":141037,"text":"They laughed. They dismissed us."},{"time":143023,"text":"They said, \"You know what? Indians don't do innovation.\""},{"time":146030,"text":"The more polite ones said, \"Well, you know, Indians"},{"time":148060,"text":"make good software programmers and accountants,"},{"time":151067,"text":"but they can't do the creative stuff.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":154017,"text":"Sometimes, it took a more, took a veneer of sophistication,"},{"time":158083,"text":"and people said, \"You know, it's nothing to do with Indians."},{"time":161033,"text":"It's really the rule-based, regimented education system"},{"time":164094,"text":"in India that is responsible for killing all creativity.\""},{"time":169032,"text":"They said, instead, if you want to see real creativity,"},{"time":171086,"text":"go to Silicon Valley, and look at companies"},{"time":173085,"text":"like Google, Microsoft, Intel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176051,"text":"So we started examining the R&amp;amp;D and innovation labs"},{"time":179005,"text":"of Silicon Valley."},{"time":181057,"text":"Well, interestingly, what you find there is,"},{"time":183071,"text":"usually you are introduced to the head of the innovation lab"},{"time":186064,"text":"or the R&amp;amp;D center as they may call it,"},{"time":188061,"text":"and more often than not, it's an Indian. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":192024,"text":"So I immediately said, \"Well, but you could not have been"},{"time":195027,"text":"educated in India, right?"},{"time":196062,"text":"You must have gotten your education here.\""},{"time":198018,"text":"It turned out, in every single case,"},{"time":202004,"text":"they came out of the Indian educational system."},{"time":206026,"text":"So we realized that maybe we had the wrong question,"},{"time":208075,"text":"and the right question is, really, can Indians"},{"time":211062,"text":"based out of India do innovative work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215042,"text":"So off we went to India. We made, I think,"},{"time":217070,"text":"about a dozen trips to Bangalore, Mumbai, Gurgaon,"},{"time":220092,"text":"Delhi, Hyderabad, you name it, to examine"},{"time":223011,"text":"what is the level of corporate innovation in these cities."},{"time":228036,"text":"And what we found was, as we progressed in our research,"},{"time":230094,"text":"was, that we were asking really the wrong question."},{"time":233090,"text":"When you ask, \"Where are the Indian Googles,"},{"time":235065,"text":"iPods and Viagras?\" you are taking a particular perspective"},{"time":239099,"text":"on innovation, which is innovation for end users,"},{"time":244015,"text":"visible innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245078,"text":"Instead, innovation, if you remember, some of you"},{"time":249047,"text":"may have read the famous economist Schumpeter,"},{"time":251048,"text":"he said, \"Innovation is novelty"},{"time":253055,"text":"in how value is created and distributed.\""},{"time":257031,"text":"It could be new products and services,"},{"time":259044,"text":"but it could also be new ways of producing products."},{"time":261077,"text":"It could also be novel ways of organizing firms and industries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264091,"text":"Once you take this, there's no reason to restrict innovation,"},{"time":268077,"text":"the beneficiaries of innovation, just to end users."},{"time":272077,"text":"When you take this broader conceptualization of innovation,"},{"time":275038,"text":"what we found was, India is well represented"},{"time":278072,"text":"in innovation, but the innovation that is being done in India"},{"time":282006,"text":"is of a form we did not anticipate, and what we did was"},{"time":285026,"text":"we called it \"invisible innovation.\""},{"time":287091,"text":"And specifically, there are four types of invisible innovation"},{"time":290078,"text":"that are coming out of India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292098,"text":"The first type of invisible innovation out of India"},{"time":295068,"text":"is what we call innovation for business customers,"},{"time":298057,"text":"which is led by the multinational corporations,"},{"time":301042,"text":"which have -- in the last two decades, there have been"},{"time":304035,"text":"750 R&amp;amp;D centers set up in India by multinational companies"},{"time":310064,"text":"employing more than 400,000 professionals."},{"time":314086,"text":"Now, when you consider the fact that, historically,"},{"time":319012,"text":"the R&amp;amp;D center of a multinational company"},{"time":322029,"text":"was always in the headquarters, or in the country of origin"},{"time":326098,"text":"of that multinational company, to have 750 R&amp;amp;D centers"},{"time":330088,"text":"of multinational corporations in India"},{"time":333025,"text":"is truly a remarkable figure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":335082,"text":"When we went and talked to the people in those innovation"},{"time":338005,"text":"centers and asked them what are they working on,"},{"time":340066,"text":"they said, \"We are working on global products.\""},{"time":342076,"text":"They were not working on localizing global products"},{"time":345039,"text":"for India, which is the usual role of a local R&amp;amp;D."},{"time":349011,"text":"They were working on truly global products,"},{"time":351061,"text":"and companies like Microsoft, Google, AstraZeneca,"},{"time":355037,"text":"General Electric, Philips, have already answered"},{"time":358024,"text":"in the affirmative the question that from their Bangalore"},{"time":361072,"text":"and Hyderabad R&amp;amp;D centers they are able to produce"},{"time":365067,"text":"products and services for the world."},{"time":368069,"text":"But of course, as an end user, you don't see that,"},{"time":371036,"text":"because you only see the name of the company,"},{"time":372087,"text":"not where it was developed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376064,"text":"The other thing we were told then was, \"Yes, but, you know,"},{"time":379048,"text":"the kind of work that is coming out of the Indian R&amp;amp;D center"},{"time":381072,"text":"cannot be compared to the kind of work that is coming out"},{"time":383075,"text":"of the U.S. R&amp;amp;D centers.\""},{"time":386010,"text":"So my coauthor Phanish Puranam, who happens to be"},{"time":387071,"text":"one of the smartest people I know, said"},{"time":390008,"text":"he's going to do a study."},{"time":391053,"text":"What he did was he looked at those companies"},{"time":394019,"text":"that had an R&amp;amp;D center in USA and in India,"},{"time":397090,"text":"and then he looked at a patent that was filed"},{"time":400047,"text":"out of the U.S. and a similar patent filed out of the same"},{"time":403018,"text":"company's subsidiary in India,"},{"time":405068,"text":"so he's now comparing the patents of R&amp;amp;D centers"},{"time":408076,"text":"in the U.S. with R&amp;amp;D centers in India of the same company"},{"time":412077,"text":"to find out what is the quality of the patents filed"},{"time":415007,"text":"out of the Indian centers and how do they compare"},{"time":416094,"text":"with the quality of the patents filed out of the U.S. centers?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419073,"text":"Interestingly, what he finds is"},{"time":421094,"text":"— and by the way, the way we look at the quality of a patent"},{"time":424065,"text":"is what we call forward citations: How many times"},{"time":427055,"text":"does a future patent reference the older patent? —"},{"time":431072,"text":"he finds something very interesting."},{"time":434023,"text":"What we find is that the data says"},{"time":436091,"text":"that the number of forward citations of a patent filed"},{"time":440010,"text":"out of a U.S. R&amp;amp;D subsidiary is identical to the number"},{"time":443051,"text":"of forward citations of a patent filed by an Indian subsidiary"},{"time":447023,"text":"of the same company within that company."},{"time":449044,"text":"So within the company, there's no difference in the forward"},{"time":452035,"text":"citation rates of their Indian subsidiaries versus"},{"time":454086,"text":"their U.S. subsidiaries."},{"time":455096,"text":"So that's the first kind of invisible innovation coming out of India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459078,"text":"The second kind of invisible innovation coming out of India"},{"time":462033,"text":"is what we call outsourcing innovation to Indian companies,"},{"time":466003,"text":"where many companies today are contracting"},{"time":469005,"text":"Indian companies to do a major part of their product"},{"time":472097,"text":"development work for their global products"},{"time":477038,"text":"which are going to be sold to the entire world."},{"time":479069,"text":"For example, in the pharma industry, a lot of the molecules"},{"time":481091,"text":"are being developed, but you see a major part of that work"},{"time":484051,"text":"is being sent to India."},{"time":487006,"text":"For example, XCL Technologies,"},{"time":490007,"text":"they developed two of the mission critical systems"},{"time":492099,"text":"for the new Boeing 787 Dreamliner,"},{"time":496019,"text":"one to avoid collisions in the sky,"},{"time":498091,"text":"and another to allow landing in zero visibility."},{"time":502015,"text":"But of course, when you climb onto the Boeing 787,"},{"time":504078,"text":"you are not going to know that this is invisible innovation"},{"time":507016,"text":"out of India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508043,"text":"The third kind of invisible innovation coming out of India"},{"time":511044,"text":"is what we call process innovations, because of an injection"},{"time":514043,"text":"of intelligence by Indian firms."},{"time":517016,"text":"Process innovation is different from product innovation."},{"time":521042,"text":"It's about how do you create a new product or develop"},{"time":524063,"text":"a new product or manufacture a new product,"},{"time":526063,"text":"but not a new product itself?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528067,"text":"Only in India do millions of young people dream"},{"time":533077,"text":"of working in a call center."},{"time":537096,"text":"What happens — You know, it's a dead end job in the West,"},{"time":540098,"text":"what high school dropouts do."},{"time":543031,"text":"What happens when you put hundreds of thousands"},{"time":546043,"text":"of smart, young, ambitious kids"},{"time":549059,"text":"on a call center job?"},{"time":551089,"text":"Very quickly, they get bored, and they start innovating,"},{"time":556079,"text":"and they start telling the boss how to do this job better, and"},{"time":560009,"text":"out of this process innovation comes product innovations,"},{"time":563030,"text":"which are then marketed around the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565003,"text":"For example, 24/7 Customer,"},{"time":567042,"text":"traditional call center company, used to be a traditional"},{"time":569071,"text":"call center company. Today they're developing"},{"time":571055,"text":"analytical tools to do predictive modeling so that before"},{"time":575000,"text":"you pick up the phone, you can guess"},{"time":578005,"text":"or predict what this phone call is about."},{"time":584078,"text":"It's because of an injection of intelligence into a process"},{"time":587028,"text":"which was considered dead for a long time in the West."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590010,"text":"And the last kind of innovation, invisible innovation"},{"time":593041,"text":"coming out of India is what we call management innovation."},{"time":596002,"text":"It's not a new product or a new process"},{"time":597075,"text":"but a new way to organize work,"},{"time":600010,"text":"and the most significant management innovation to come"},{"time":602059,"text":"out of India, invented by the Indian offshoring industry"},{"time":606015,"text":"is what we call the global delivery model."},{"time":608080,"text":"What the global delivery model allows is, it allows you"},{"time":611009,"text":"to take previously geographically core-located tasks,"},{"time":614059,"text":"break them up into parts, send them around the world"},{"time":617060,"text":"where the expertise and the cost structure exists,"},{"time":619061,"text":"and then specify the means for reintegrating them."},{"time":622044,"text":"Without that, you could not have any of the other"},{"time":624057,"text":"invisible innovations today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626085,"text":"So, what I'm trying to say is, what we are finding"},{"time":629049,"text":"in our research is, that if products for end users"},{"time":634012,"text":"is the visible tip of the innovation iceberg,"},{"time":637041,"text":"India is well represented in the invisible, large,"},{"time":641033,"text":"submerged portion of the innovation iceberg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646057,"text":"Now, this has, of course, some implications,"},{"time":651053,"text":"and so we developed three implications of this research."},{"time":655077,"text":"The first is what we called sinking skill ladder,"},{"time":659001,"text":"and now I'm going to go back to where I started my"},{"time":661073,"text":"conversation with you, which was about the flight of jobs."},{"time":664095,"text":"Now, of course, when we first, as a multinational company,"},{"time":668008,"text":"decide to outsource jobs to India in the R&amp;amp;D,"},{"time":670090,"text":"what we are going to do is we are going to outsource the"},{"time":674034,"text":"bottom rung of the ladder to India, the least sophisticated jobs,"},{"time":677042,"text":"just like Tom Friedman would predict."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680063,"text":"Now, what happens is, when you outsource the bottom rung"},{"time":683035,"text":"of the ladder to India for innovation and for R&amp;amp;D work,"},{"time":688017,"text":"at some stage in the very near future you are going to have"},{"time":691040,"text":"to confront a problem,"},{"time":693054,"text":"which is where does the next step"},{"time":695043,"text":"of the ladder people come from within your company?"},{"time":698069,"text":"So you have two choices then:"},{"time":701059,"text":"Either you bring the people from India into"},{"time":703077,"text":"the developed world to take positions in the next step"},{"time":706068,"text":"of the ladder — immigration —"},{"time":709042,"text":"or you say, there's so many people in the bottom step"},{"time":711086,"text":"of the ladder waiting to take the next position in India,"},{"time":714050,"text":"why don't we move the next step to India?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":718073,"text":"What we are trying to say is"},{"time":720068,"text":"that once you outsource the bottom end of the ladder, you --"},{"time":725091,"text":"it's a self-perpetuating act, because of the sinking skill ladder,"},{"time":728061,"text":"and the sinking skill ladder is simply the point that"},{"time":731034,"text":"you can't be an investment banker"},{"time":733049,"text":"without having been an analyst once."},{"time":735048,"text":"You can't be a professor without having been a student."},{"time":737075,"text":"You can't be a consultant without having been a research associate."},{"time":740061,"text":"So, if you outsource the least sophisticated jobs,"},{"time":743020,"text":"at some stage, the next step of the ladder has to follow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747047,"text":"The second thing we bring up is what we call"},{"time":749032,"text":"the browning of the TMT, the top management teams."},{"time":752068,"text":"If the R&amp;amp;D talent is going to be based out of India"},{"time":755032,"text":"and China, and the largest growth markets"},{"time":757056,"text":"are going to be based out of India and China,"},{"time":759080,"text":"you have to confront the problem that"},{"time":761053,"text":"your top management of the future"},{"time":763015,"text":"is going to have to come out of India and China,"},{"time":766016,"text":"because that's where the product leadership is,"},{"time":767099,"text":"that's where the important market leadership is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770015,"text":"Right? And the last thing we point out in this slide,"},{"time":772093,"text":"which is, you know, that to this story, there's one caveat."},{"time":776036,"text":"India has the youngest growing population in the world."},{"time":780042,"text":"This demographic dividend is incredible, but paradoxically,"},{"time":784072,"text":"there's also the mirage of mighty labor pools."},{"time":787011,"text":"Indian institutes and educational system,"},{"time":790004,"text":"with a few exceptions, are incapable of producing students"},{"time":792097,"text":"in the quantity and quality needed"},{"time":795047,"text":"to keep this innovation engine going,"},{"time":798001,"text":"so companies are finding innovative ways to overcome this,"},{"time":801022,"text":"but in the end it does not absolve the government"},{"time":803082,"text":"of the responsibility for creating this educational structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808029,"text":"So finally, I want to conclude"},{"time":811062,"text":"by showing you the profile of one company, IBM."},{"time":814094,"text":"As many of you know, IBM has always been considered"},{"time":817031,"text":"for the last hundred years to be one of the most"},{"time":819029,"text":"innovative companies."},{"time":820056,"text":"In fact, if you look at the number of patents filed over history,"},{"time":823031,"text":"I think they are in the top or the top two or three companies"},{"time":825071,"text":"in the world of all patents filed in the USA as a private company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829041,"text":"Here is the profile of employees of"},{"time":831091,"text":"IBM over the last decade."},{"time":835084,"text":"In 2003, they had 300,000 employees,"},{"time":838059,"text":"or 330,000 employees, out of which, 135,000"},{"time":842068,"text":"were in America, 9,000 were in India."},{"time":846027,"text":"In 2009, they had 400,000 employees, by which time"},{"time":851030,"text":"the U.S. employees had moved to 105,000,"},{"time":853087,"text":"whereas the Indian employees had gone to 100,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":857014,"text":"Well, in 2010, they decided they're not going to reveal"},{"time":860016,"text":"this data anymore, so I had to make some estimates"},{"time":862048,"text":"based on various sources."},{"time":863088,"text":"Here are my best guesses. Okay? I'm not saying"},{"time":866052,"text":"this is the exact number, it's my best guess."},{"time":867098,"text":"It gives you a sense of the trend."},{"time":869060,"text":"There are 433,000 people now at IBM, out of which"},{"time":874023,"text":"98,000 are remaining in the U.S.,"},{"time":876083,"text":"and 150,000 are in India."},{"time":880039,"text":"So you tell me, is IBM an American company,"},{"time":883051,"text":"or an Indian company? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":887057,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}